sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is an Autotransporter of the AT-1 family from the organism Neisseria meningitidis. Autotransporters are proteins that form a pore in the outermembrane and and pull their N terminus through this pore in order to expose it to the extracellular space. N-terminal fusions of proteins to this part may permit the cell surface display of the fused protein.
